gps.name: GPSLatitudeRef
gps.notes:
tags 0x0001-0x0006 used for camera location according to MWG 2.0. ExifTool
            will also accept a number when writing GPSLatitudeRef, positive for north
            latitudes or negative for south, or a string containing N, North, S or South

gps.name: GPSDateStamp
gps.notes:
when writing, time is stripped off if present, after adjusting date/time to
            UTC if time includes a timezone.  Format is YYYY:mm:dd

gps.name: GPSProcessingMethod
gps.notes: values of "GPS", "CELLID", "WLAN" or "MANUAL" by the EXIF spec.

gps.name: GPSAltitudeRef
gps.notes:
ExifTool will also accept number when writing this tag, with negative
            numbers indicating below sea level

gps.name: GPSDestLatitudeRef
gps.notes: tags 0x0013-0x001a used for subject location according to MWG 2.0

gps.name: GPSLongitudeRef
gps.notes:
ExifTool will also accept a number when writing this tag, positive for east
            longitudes or negative for west, or a string containing E, East, W or West

gps.name: GPSTimeStamp
gps.notes:
UTC time of GPS fix.  When writing, date is stripped off if present, and
            time is adjusted to UTC if it includes a timezone

main.name: ResolutionUnit
main.notes: the value 1 is not standard EXIF

main.name: ThumbnailOffset
WB_GRGBLevels
main.notes: found in IFD0 of Leaf MOS images

main.name: SubSecTime
main.notes: fractional seconds for ModifyDate

main.name: FocalPlaneResolutionUnit
main.notes: values 1, 4 and 5 are not standard EXIF

main.name: MDFileTag
main.notes: tags 0x82a5-0x82ac are used in Molecular Dynamics GEL files

main.name: OffsetTimeDigitized
main.notes: time zone for CreateDate

main.name: PixelFormat
main.notes:
tags 0xbc** are used in Windows HD Photo (HDP and WDP) images. The actual
            PixelFormat values are 16-byte GUID's but the leading 15 bytes,
            '6fddc324-4e03-4bfe-b1853-d77768dc9', have been removed below to avoid
            unnecessary clutter

main.name: MaxApertureValue
main.notes: displayed as an F number, but stored as an APEX value

main.name: SEMInfo
main.notes: found in some scanning electron microscope images

main.name: OriginalBestQualitySize
main.notes: called OriginalBestQualityFinalSize by the DNG spec

main.name: DateTimeOriginal
main.notes: date/time when original image was taken

main.name: ExposureCompensation
main.notes: called ExposureBiasValue by the EXIF spec.

main.name: SubfileType
main.notes: called NewSubfileType by the TIFF specification

values.3: Single page of multi-page reduced-resolution image
values.7: Transparency mask of reduced-resolution multi-page image

main.name: ExifImageWidth
main.notes: called PixelXDimension by the EXIF spec.

main.name: OwnerName
main.notes: called CameraOwnerName by the EXIF spec.

main.name: SubSecTimeOriginal
main.notes: fractional seconds for DateTimeOriginal

main.name: Artist
main.notes: becomes a list-type tag when the MWG module is loaded

main.name: OwnerName
main.notes:
tags 0xfde8-0xfdea and 0xfe4c-0xfe58 are generated by Photoshop Camera RAW.
            Some names are the same as other EXIF tags, but ExifTool will avoid writing
            these unless they already exist in the file

main.name: ShutterSpeedValue
main.notes: displayed in seconds, but stored as an APEX value

main.name: OffsetTime
main.notes: time zone for ModifyDate

main.name: DNGPrivateData
main.notes: Provides a way for camera manufacturers to store private data in the DNG file for use by their own raw converters, and to have that data preserved by programs that edit DNG files.

values.3: Highpass and LowPass Frequency Data Discarded

main.name: ColorSpace
main.notes:
the value of 0x2 is not standard EXIF.  Instead, an Adobe RGB image is
            indicated by "Uncalibrated" with an InteropIndex of "R03".  The values
            0xfffd and 0xfffe are also non-standard, and are used by some Sony cameras

main.name: ISO
main.notes:
called ISOSpeedRatings by EXIF 2.2, then PhotographicSensitivity by the EXIF
            2.3 spec.

main.name: SubSecTimeDigitized
main.notes: fractional seconds for CreateDate

main.name: ExifImageHeight
main.notes: called PixelYDimension by the EXIF spec.

main.name: SerialNumber
main.notes: called BodySerialNumber by the EXIF spec.

main.name: OffsetTimeOriginal
main.notes: time zone for DateTimeOriginal

main.name: TimeZoneOffset
main.notes:
1 or 2 values: 1. The time zone offset of DateTimeOriginal from GMT in
            hours, 2. If present, the time zone offset of ModifyDate

main.name: SampleFormat
main.notes: SamplesPerPixel values

main.name: Humidity
main.notes: ambient relative humidity in percent

main.name: ChromaticAberrationCorrParams
main.notes: found in Sony ARW images

main.name: AmbientTemperature
main.notes: ambient temperature in degrees C, called Temperature by the EXIF spec.

main.name: OldSubfileType
main.notes: called SubfileType by the TIFF specification

main.name: LensInfo
main.notes:
4 rational values giving focal and aperture ranges, called LensSpecification
            by the EXIF spec.

main.name: SceneCaptureType
main.notes: the value of 4 is non-standard, and used by some Samsung models

main.name: GeoTiffDirectory
main.notes:
these "GeoTiff" tags may read and written as a block, but they aren't
            extracted unless specifically requested.  Byte order changes are handled
            automatically when copying between TIFF images with different byte order

main.name: RelatedImageHeight
main.notes: called RelatedImageLength by the DCF spec.

values.6: Even rows offset up by 1/2 row, even columns offset left by 1/2 column
values.7: Even rows offset up by 1/2 row, even columns offset right by 1/2 column
values.8: Even rows offset down by 1/2 row, even columns offset left by 1/2 column
values.9: Even rows offset down by 1/2 row, even columns offset right by 1/2 column

main.name: DistortionCorrParams
main.notes: found in Sony ARW images

main.name: SubIFDs
main.notes: Defined by Adobe Corporation to enable TIFF Trees within a TIFF file.

main.name: Pressure
main.notes: air pressure in hPa or mbar

main.name: VignettingCorrection
main.notes: found in Sony ARW images

values.34718: Microsoft Document Imaging (MDI) Binary Level Codec
values.34719: Microsoft Document Imaging (MDI) Progressive Transform Codec

main.name: FocalLengthIn35mmFormat
main.notes: called FocalLengthIn35mmFilm by the EXIF spec.

main.name: ImageHeight
main.notes: called ImageLength by the EXIF spec.

values.3: Highpass and LowPass Frequency Data Discarded

main.name: DNGVersion
main.notes:
tags 0xc612-0xcd3b are defined by the DNG specification unless otherwise
            noted.  See L<https://helpx.adobe.com/photoshop/digital-negative.html> for
            the specification

main.name: WaterDepth
main.notes: depth under water in metres, negative for above water

main.name: Copyright
main.notes:
may contain copyright notices for photographer and editor, separated by a
            newline.  As per the EXIF specification, the newline is replaced by a null
            byte when writing to file, but this may be avoided by disabling the print
            conversion

main.name: CustomRendered
main.notes:
only 0 and 1 are standard EXIF, but other values are used by Apple iOS
            devices

main.name: PanasonicTitle
main.notes: proprietary Panasonic tag used for baby/pet name, etc

main.name: Acceleration
main.notes: directionless camera acceleration in units of mGal, or 10-5 m/s2

main.name: Opto-ElectricConvFactor
main.notes: called OECF by the EXIF spec.

main.name: KDC_IFD
main.notes: used in some Kodak KDC images

main.name: ProcessingSoftware
main.notes: used by ACD Systems Digital Imaging

main.name: OffsetSchema
main.notes: Microsoft's ill-conceived maker note offset difference

main.name: DepthFormat
main.notes: tags 0xc7e9-0xc7ee added by DNG 1.5.0.0

main.name: StripOffsets
main.notes:
called StripOffsets in most locations, but it is PreviewImageStart in IFD0
                of CR2 images and various IFD's of DNG images except for SubIFD2 where it is
                JpgFromRawStart

main.name: VignettingCorrParams
main.notes: found in Sony ARW images

main.name: KodakIFD
main.notes: used in various types of Kodak images

main.name: PanasonicTitle2
main.notes: proprietary Panasonic tag used for baby/pet name with age

values.93: Auto, Fired, Red-eye reduction, Return not detected

main.name: SensitivityType
main.notes: applies to EXIF:ISO tag

values.5: Standard Output Sensitivity and ISO Speed
values.6: Recommended Exposure Index and ISO Speed
values.7: Standard Output Sensitivity, Recommended Exposure Index and ISO Speed

main.name: RawImageSegmentation
main.notes:
used in segmented Canon CR2 images.  3 numbers: 1. Number of segments minus
            one; 2. Pixel width of segments except last; 3. Pixel width of last segment

main.name: CreateDate
main.notes: called DateTimeDigitized by the EXIF spec.

main.name: CompositeImageExposureTimes
main.notes:
11 or more values: 1. Total exposure time period, 2. Total exposure of all
            source images, 3. Total exposure of all used images, 4. Max exposure time of
            source images, 5. Max exposure time of used images, 6. Min exposure time of
            source images, 7. Min exposure of used images, 8. Number of sequences, 9.
            Number of source images in sequence. 10-N. Exposure times of each source
            image. Called SourceExposureTimesOfCompositeImage by the EXIF spec.

main.name: XPAuthor
main.notes: ignored by Windows Explorer if Artist exists

main.name: DistortionCorrection
main.notes: found in Sony ARW images

main.name: XPTitle
main.notes:
tags 0x9c9b-0x9c9f are used by Windows Explorer; special characters
            in these values are converted to UTF-8 by default, or Windows Latin1
            with the -L option.  XPTitle is ignored by Windows Explorer if
            ImageDescription exists

values.0: Higher resolution image does not exist

main.name: StripByteCounts
main.notes: The total number of bytes in each strip. With JPEG compressed data this designation is not needed and is omitted.

main.name: ThumbnailLength

main.description: A tag for manufacturers of Exif writers to record any desired information. The contents are up to the manufacturer.
